&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ass&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;istant Practitioner - Diabetes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 4&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent, Full Time (37.5 hours per week)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a new and innovative role as an Assistant Practitioner in Diabetes, Band 4.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is to support the diabetes specialist nurse team based on Aintree Hospital site assisting in the delivery of treatment, education and care for people with diabetes and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will coordinate the smooth running of a busy Diabetes outpatient department in the diabetes centre at Aintree and also working with the Liverpool Diabetes partnership community team. The post holder will maintain data bases including insulin pumps and continuous monitoring devices. The Assistant Practitioner will ensure effective communication with patients, carers, multidisciplinary team and the wider health and social care community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;If you think this is the role for you then please contact for further information&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
